HEADWORD: Amotion
<hw>A*mo"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>amotio</ets>. See <er>Amove</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Removal;
ousting; especially, the removal of a corporate officer from his
office.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deprivation of possession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amotus</ent>⟦br⟧
